to be implemented in nutrition section 
What Needs Implementation:

1. Food Logging System:

Log Food Form (similar to medication logging)

Daily Food Entries (multiple meals per day)

Food Database Integration (auto-calculate calories)

2. Water Logging Enhancement:

Manual Water Entry (beyond quick-add buttons)

Daily Water Goals (based on weight)

Time-stamped Entries

3. History Views:

30-Day Food History with filtering

30-Day Water History with trends

Monthly Summary (total calories, avg water)

4. Export Features:

CSV Export for both food and water logs

PDF Reports with charts

Date Range Selection for exports

Core Missing Pieces:

Food entry form UI

Persistent food log storage

History display templates

Export functionality

The water logging works but needs manual entry option. Food logging doesn't exist yet beyond the placeholder.

Your Approach is Spot On:
Phase 1: Enhance Current Structure

Keep all existing nutrition calculator logic

Add food logging to the current feeding schedule

Integrate water intake into the feeding form

Implement basic food bag calculator

Phase 2: Smart Water Integration

Add daily water intake field to feeding form

Use condition/age/breed/weight to calculate expected water intake

Compare actual vs expected water consumption

Generate alerts for polydipsia (excessive drinking) or oligodipsia (reduced drinking)

The Smart Water Logic You're Describing:
text
DAILY WATER INTAKE CALCULATOR:
Expected: (50ml × 4kg) + (food moisture) = 250ml daily
Actual: 180ml logged today
ALERT: "Water intake 28% below expected for kidney cat"
For Kidney Cats (Your Use Case):

Expected: Higher water needs to support kidney function

Alert: "Reduced water intake - kidney risk increased"

Suggestion: "Consider wet food or water fountain"

For Diabetes:
Expected: Normal range based on weight

Alert: "Excessive water intake - possible glucose issues"

The Formulas We Can Implement:
Basic Water Needs:

Dogs: 50-60ml per kg of body weight

Cats: 40-50ml per kg of body weight

Adjust for: Dry food (+20%), Hot weather (+15%), Activity level

Condition Modifiers:

Kidney disease: +20-30% water needs

Diabetes: Monitor for excessive intake

Hyperthyroidism: Increased needs

Implementation Flow:
User logs daily feeding
     ↓
[Auto-calculate expected water intake]
     ↓
[User enters actual water consumed]
     ↓
[System compares actual vs expected]
     ↓
[Condition-based alerts generated]
     ↓
"Kidney cat drinking 40% less than recommended"

